    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>National Briefing | Rockies: Colorado: Air Force Is Sued Over Religion</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Laurie Goodstein (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Goodstein, Laurie</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Air Force Academy graduate Mikey Weinstein files suit in New Mexico against Air Force and acting secretary Pete Geren, claiming Air Force encourages evangelical Christians to proselytize academy cadets; Weinstein says his two sons were subjected to proselytizing when they attended academy (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A critic of the Air Force Academy filed suit against the Air Force and its acting secretary, Pete Geren, claiming that the Air Force encourages evangelical Christians to proselytize cadets at the academy. The critic, Mikey Weinstein, a Jewish graduate of the academy whose two sons have attended the school in Colorado Springs, asserts that senior officers and cadets have tried to impose evangelical Christianity on his sons. The Air Force sent a team of investigators to the academy this year and issued new guidelines on religious expression in August. The suit was filed in federal court in New Mexico, where Mr. Weinstein lives.</p>
        <p>Laurie Goodstein (NYT)</p>
      </block>
